use xed to open a document with text editor

create readme, local git repository, commit readme, move to branch main, add remote repository, and push main:

echo "# test" >> README.md
git init
git add README.md
git commit -m "first commit"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin git@github.com:amplifiedcactus/test.git
git push -u origin main

how to get files from remote repository to local one:
git clone git@github.com:amplifiedcactus/test.git
cd test
git checkout main (to switch to a different branch)

sudo minicom -D /dev/ttyACM0 -b 115200

picotool load -f build/src/hello_freertos.elf
picotool reboot

cmake -B build -S .
cmake --build build

